QueryText: asked about vareities of cluster bean ?
KCCAns:
Pusa Evergreen - It is growing upright and tall and it is recommended for summer and kharif season. These breed pods are 12 to 15 cm long, while the legumes are green, fresh and unbinned. Beginning of groundnut begins 45 to 55 days.
Pusa nayabahar - It gives good yields during both summer and kharif season. Peanuts are of 15cm long greenish green color. There is a direct increase of the trees. The leaf is a ghost of groundnut.
Pusa Seasonal - This product is good for kharif season and the breed of this breed is 10 to 12 cm long and it can be harvested in 75 to 80 days. The beans are attractive, shiny, greenish. In this species, the branches should be broken in a large quantity and the pods reach the top of the main trunk and branches.
Sharad Bahar - The tree is tall, the tree has 10 to 14 branches. Pendants are attractive, soft, rosarous, long-lived. This is suitable for Kharif season.

Seeds should be sown on the bed up to make seedlings. Before preparing the bed plant, make sure to double the soil by placing 2, 3 cloves of the cluster and fry the land. Gadi wafa is 1m The width should be 3 meters long and 15 cm tall. Grind 1 gram Fenugreek, mix 50 grams of soyafa and make the steam flat with the hand. Before sowing, wash 3 grams of thyroid fungicide. Planting of seeds should be planted with parallel fingers by cutting the waist and covering it with soil. Water should be provided with fenugreek leaves. After coming out of seed, after 10 to 12 days, give two grams of pearl in two rows and give 10 gram frontlets per foot. Keep the steam watered. To control the flowering and crushing disease, spray 15 days after seedling with 12 to 15 ml monochrotocos and 25 gm of diaethene-M-45 in 10 liters of water. The next two sprays should be done at intervals of 10 days. After 25 to 30 days of sowing, ie after seedling height of 12-15 cm, seedlings should be restored to the entire world. Give water to the vapor a day before planting the seedlings. Therefore, the seedlings are not easily damaged due to the roots of the seedlings. For more wheat production, there should be 20 to 22 lakh hectares of trees in the field. For this, 1oo kg of seeds per hectare should be used for sowing time.
Due to low temperature for late sowing, due to low wheat foliage the seed should be kept in the ratio of 125 to 150 kg per hectare. Seed treatment should be used for seeding of 75-100 kg per hectare.
Before sowing, seeds should be processed in the quantity of Captain or Thayaram fungicide with 3 gm per kg seed.
